    "comment": "Rationale: The authors investigate the role of PLCs in long-term depression (LTD) in the visual cortex. They find that knockout of PLC-b1 abolishes LTD in this preparation (Figure 6A). This appears to be a postsynaptic effect, because postsynaptic superfusion with the PLC antagonist U73112 (U...2) also blocks LTD (Figure 6B).\n\n24/11/2017 Pim\n- Since the authors investigate the site of action, I allow annotation to the postsynaptic process.. Experimental description: To directly test the involvement of PLC in LTD,we used slices prepared from mice lacking the b1 isoform of PLC (PLC b1).",
